key_insights.description: The 2024 curriculum has 499 more learning objectives than the 2018 version, suggesting expanded coverage of learning outcomes.
The most substantially increased terms in the 2024 curriculum are belirle, ilişkin, varsayım, suggesting new or expanded emphasis in these areas.
The most substantially decreased terms in the 2024 curriculum are ver, yer, iletişim, suggesting reduced emphasis in these areas.
The 'algebra' domain shows the largest increase in coverage (+120), suggesting expanded emphasis in this area of mathematics.
The percentage of objectives demanding higher-order thinking skills (analyze, evaluate, create) has increased by 9.0%, suggesting more emphasis on advanced cognitive skills in the 2024 curriculum.
